The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Beyond Boundaries, the first international alumni meet of St Xaviers College, Calcutta, that was to be held in Bangkok on May 22 and 23, has been postponed because of violence and unrest in the Thailand capital. The event would be held on July 24 and 25 at same venue. The list of attractions, including performances by Shubhen Chatterjee and Bickram Ghosh and a fashion show by designer Agnimitra Paul, remains unchanged.     Jogender Singh, a 32-year-old resident of Narkeldanga Main Road, committed suicide by jumping in front of a Kavi Nazrul-bound Metro Railway train at Chandni Chowk station on Wednesday. Metro services were disrupted from 8.07 pm to 8.51 pm.    The body of 13-year-old Purnima Bag, a resident of Joypur in Howrahs Uluberia, was found in a bush near her home on Wednesday morning. Police said Purnima was missing since Sunday evening. Her family members alleged that she was raped and murdered. The body has been sent for post-mortem and a murder case started.    Debu Swami, 45, was caught while allegedly stealing Rs 1.5 lakh from the office of the head cashier of the Bally branch of Allahabad Bank on Wednesday. He had sneaked into the office around 12.45pm. Officials and customers caught Swami, who was handed over to police.                                                                                                                                                  
